'''Agnihotram Ramanuja Tatachariar''' (1907&ndash;2008) was a renowned [[Vedic]] scholar of [[Vaishnava]] sect of [[Hinduism]]. He was a descendant of [[Nathamuni]] hailing from [[Kumbakonam]]. He was recipient of two national awards for his contribution to Vedic studies and [[Sanskrit]] literature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newstodaynet.com/printer.php?id%3D9806 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-05-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100213161220/http://newstodaynet.com/printer.php?id=9806 |archivedate=2010-02-13 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://www.thehindu.com/2008/12/30/stories/2008123055101100.htm</ref>
