{{About|the Book of Mormon figure|the Filipino Mythological figure|Ama-ron}}
:''Amoron should not be confused with [[Amaron]], [[Ammaron]], [[Ammoron]] or [[Moron (Book of Mormon)]] four other Book of Mormon figures with similar names.''
{{Religious text primary|date=October 2011}}


According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Amoron''' ({{IPAc-en|ə|ˈ|m|ɔːr|ɒ|n}})<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «a-mōr´än»</ref> was a [[Nephite]] from the fifth century AD, and was a contemporary and subordinate of the [[prophet]] and army commander [[Mormon (Book of Mormon prophet)|Mormon]]. During the final war between the [[Lamanites]] and [[Nephites]], Amoron reported to Mormon.

