[[File:British Museum Hornedjitef.jpg|thumb|The upper part of the inner coffin of Hornedjitef.]]
'''Hornedjitef''' was an [[Ancient Egypt]]ian priest in the [[Precinct of Amun-Re|Temple of Amun]] at [[Karnak]] during the reign of [[Ptolemy III]] (246-222 BC). He is known from his elaborate coffins, mummy mask and mummy, dating from the [[Ptolemaic dynasty|Early Ptolemaic Period]] (around 220 BC) and excavated from Asasif, Thebes, Egypt, which are all held in the [[British Museum]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/o/outer_coffin_of_the_priest_h-1.aspx |title=Outer coffin of the priest Hornedjitef |publisher=British Museum |date= |accessdate=2010-06-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100706100551/http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/o/outer_coffin_of_the_priest_h-1.aspx |archivedate=2010-07-06 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/i/inner_coffin_of_the_priest_h-1.aspx |title=Mummy of Hornedjitef › The British Museum |publisher=Britishmuseum.org |date= |accessdate=2010-06-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100123011525/http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/i/inner_coffin_of_the_priest_h-1.aspx |archivedate=2010-01-23 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/m/mummy_mask_of_hornedjitef.aspx |title=Mummy mask of Hornedjitef |publisher=British Museum |date= |accessdate=2010-06-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100310191642/http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/m/mummy_mask_of_hornedjitef.aspx |archivedate=2010-03-10 |df= }}</ref> These related objects were chosen as the first of the hundred objects selected by British Museum Director [[Neil MacGregor]] in the 2010 [[BBC Radio 4]] series ''[[A History of the World in 100 Objects]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=John Taylor, Curator, British Museum |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/ahistoryoftheworld/objects/sogITE3FSKStlk12qd2W3w |title=A History of the World - Object: Mummy of Hornedjitef |publisher=BBC |date= |accessdate=2010-06-09}}</ref>
Along with his coffins, mummy-case, mummy-mask and mummy, Hornedjitef's tomb contained items such as a papyrus [[Book of the Dead]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/research/search_the_collection_database/search_object_details.aspx?objectid=114358&partid=1&searchText=Hornedjitef&fromADBC=ad&toADBC=ad&numpages=10&orig=%2fresearch%2fsearch_the_collection_database.aspx&currentPage=2 |title=Search object details |publisher=British Museum |date= |accessdate=2010-06-09}}</ref> and a painted wooden figure of Ptah-Sokar-Osiris.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/p/painted_wooden_figure_of_ptah-.aspx |title=Painted wooden figure of Ptah-Sokar-Osiris |publisher=British Museum |date= |accessdate=2010-06-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100706100518/http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/aes/p/painted_wooden_figure_of_ptah-.aspx |archivedate=2010-07-06 |df= }}</ref>
